</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="64FE0B05B43B33981281B720B466D8FA" pageId="9" pageNumber="114" type="note">
<paragraph id="3C824F7D5F9E3A3CF2F8C7003A926BC4" pageId="9" pageNumber="114">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0D490C613DA5A785A853955C5CC33978" pageId="9" pageNumber="114">
Flowers with a short (
<taxonomicName id="6DE6D07B848206C1143D0B3D2C5591AE" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Astelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astelia subsp. sect." order="Asparagales" pageId="9" pageNumber="114" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Periastelia" species="samoënse" subSpecies="sect.">Astelia sect. Periastelia</taxonomicName>
) or long (
<taxonomicName id="11174B66F9C9F9E2685A5A79B40AF9ED" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Astelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astelia subsp. sect." order="Asparagales" pageId="9" pageNumber="114" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Tricella" species="samoënse" subSpecies="sect.">Astelia sect. Tricella</taxonomicName>
) perianth tube (0.3-3.5 mm); anthers dorsifixed, versatile; seeds ellipsoid, fusiform, or ovoid; funicle short, truncate, mucilaginous funicular hairs poorly developed; Type: 
<taxonomicName id="EA9FCE1D3C000ADB3E77DBF3DD47D891" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Astelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astelia nervosa" order="Asparagales" pageId="9" pageNumber="114" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nervosa">
<emphasis id="BCA67DFE38D3E213F7834D5792FF2300" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="114">Astelia nervosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Banks &amp; Sol. ex Hook.f., designated here.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="EEE081AB46864738F8534D4E21F4F644" pageId="9" pageNumber="114" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="6292D0B956496BEC75B0D316706136AB" pageId="9" pageNumber="114">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9D391A96E81220A8399808AAF2AA9E6C" pageId="9" pageNumber="114">
<taxonomicName id="D67F7200457534DA71CA5E747119CDAD" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Astelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astelia (Tricella) subsp. subg." order="Asparagales" pageId="9" pageNumber="114" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subGenus" species="nervosa" subGenus="Tricella" subSpecies="subg.">Astelia subg. Tricella</taxonomicName>
is revised to include both 
<taxonomicName id="A22ECE013ED62156D0F7975EEF826633" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Astelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astelia subsp. sect." order="Asparagales" pageId="9" pageNumber="114" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Tricella" species="nervosa" subSpecies="sect.">Astelia sect. Tricella</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="20F18D937192DBB6451DC64D0998A371" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Astelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astelia subsp. sect." order="Asparagales" pageId="9" pageNumber="114" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Periastelia" species="nervosa" subSpecies="sect.">Astelia sect. Periastelia</taxonomicName>
, which form a well supported clade in phylogenetic analyses (Birch unpublished PhD thesis 2011, 
<bibRefCitation id="16DFF51724F582C0C82120CCD35814D8" author="Birch, JL" journalOrPublisher="Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution" pageId="12" pageNumber="117" pagination="102 - 115" publicationUrl="10.1016/j.ympev.2012.05.031" refId="B2" refString="Birch, JL, Keeley, SC, Morden, CW, 2012. Molecular phylogeny and dating of Asteliaceae (Asparagales): Astelia s.l. evolution provides insight into the Oligocene history of New Zealand. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 65: 102 - 115, DOI: 10.1016/j.ympev.2012.05.031" title="Molecular phylogeny and dating of Asteliaceae (Asparagales): Astelia s. l. evolution provides insight into the Oligocene history of New Zealand." url="10.1016/j.ympev.2012.05.031" volume="65" year="2012">Birch et al. 2012</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="0B5CE8C51C5F9E16D56EF7D6E1D50D35" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Astelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astelia subsp. sect." order="Asparagales" pageId="9" pageNumber="114" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Periastelia" species="nervosa" subSpecies="sect.">Astelia sect. Periastelia</taxonomicName>
is monophyletic; however 
<taxonomicName id="A318CA82866BD42D0151807FFDF3F24E" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Astelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astelia subsp. sect." order="Asparagales" pageId="9" pageNumber="114" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Tricella" species="nervosa" subSpecies="sect.">Astelia sect. Tricella</taxonomicName>
is present as a grade and relationships within each of these sections remain equivocal.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
